-- Russian Equity Movers: Kuzbass Fuel, Surgutneftegas Are Active
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2012-04-04T15:52:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/russian-equity-movers-kuzbass-fuel-surgutneftegas-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 2.4
percent to 1,512.88 by the close in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index tumbled 3 percent to 1,632.21.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis:  Kuzbass Fuel Co. (KBTK)  (KBTK RX), a Russian producer of coal for
power stations, jumped 4.1 percent to 177 rubles, the highest in
a week, after reporting a 73 percent jump in fourth-quarter
profit to 776 million rubles ($26 million) and a 29 percent
increase in coal output last year, making it the country’s
fifth-largest coal exporter.  OAO RusHydro (HYDR)  (HYDR RX), the country’s biggest hydropower
generator, tumbled 3.5 percent to 1.049 rubles, its lowest level
since Jan. 18, after Kommersant newspaper reported the company
scrapped a plan to sell 63 billion rubles of treasury shares to
state-run development bank VEB.  OAO Sberbank (SBER)  (SBER RX),  Russia ’s largest bank, fell for the
first day in four as the ruble depreciated 1.2 percent against
the dollar. The stock declined 1.8 percent to 96.18 rubles.  VTB
Group (VTBR)  (VTBR RX), Russia’s second-largest bank, also declined,
retreating 3.2 percent to 6.744 kopeks.  OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGS)  (SNGS RX), the country’s fourth-largest
oil company, fell 3.4 percent to 28.756 rubles, and OAO Rosneft
(ROSN RX), Russia’s biggest oil company, declined 1.3 percent to
209.36 rubles. Oil futures slipped amid rising crude stockpiles
in the U.S. and speculation the  Federal Reserve  may refrain from
more monetary stimulus.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
